ills a significant gap in the literature and the book offers considerable original and important research-informed insights into the fields of EMI, bilingual education and second language acquisition. As such, it is a valuable resource and must-read book for researchers, practitioners and policymakers in these areas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish language-Pronunciation-Study and teaching. 0aEnglish language-Study and teaching-Foreign speakers. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Phonetics & Phonology.2bisacsh  aELF.  aEMI classroom.  aEnglish as a Lingua Franca.  aEnglish-medium degree programme.  aEnglish-medium instruction .  aICLHE.  aL2 phonology.  aSLA.  acritical period hypothesis.  aforeign accent.  ahigher education.  aimplicit learning.  alanguage learning.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishz978311061030708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019z9783110606287oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311066146040uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178892246340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781788922463423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781788922463/original  a978-3-11-061030-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-066146-0  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  a